Great question! `margin: auto` only centers horizontally because block elements don't have automatic vertical margins.

The modern approach is **Flexbox**:

```css
.parent {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: center; /* horizontal */
  align-items: center;     /* vertical */
  height: 100vh;           /* parent needs a height */
}
```

Or **CSS Grid** (even simpler):

```css
.parent {
  display: grid;
  place-items: center;
  height: 100vh;
}
```

Both methods work in all modern browsers (Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge). Flexbox gives you more control for complex layouts; Grid is the most concise for simple centering.
